h to connecting the materiality of body and sound, the social life of speech and song, and the cultural voicing of perspective and personhood.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aChurch musiczKorea (South). 0aMusiczKorea (South)xReligious aspects. 0aSingingzKorea (South). 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  aanthropology.  aart songs.  achoral music.  achristianity.  achristians.  achurch.  aconcert halls.  aculture.  aethnographic study.  aethnomusicology.  aeuropean style classical voice.  aevangelical christian.  afaith.  akorean christians.  alinguistics.  amateriality of the body.  amusic.  amusicians.  aopera.  aperformance.  apersonhood.  apolitics.  apreachers.  aprosperity.  areligion.  areligious.  aschools of music.  asemiotics.  aseoul.  asinging.  asocial transformation.  asocietal norms.  asociety.  asongs.  asound.  asouth korea.  astudy of voice.  asuperstition.  avocal and singing.  awestern opera.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052027652940uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052095740440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520957404423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520957404/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY